37498>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
37498>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
37498>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
37501>>>
37501>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37501>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37501>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37501>>>        Case Begin
37501>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37503>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37503>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37503>>>                Case Break
37504>>>                
37504>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37507>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37507>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37507>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37507>>>                Case Break
37508>>>                
37508>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37511>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37511>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37511>>>                Case Break
37512>>>                
37512>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37512>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37512>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37512>>>                  
37512>>>        Case End
37512>>>
37512>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37512>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37512>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37513>>>
37513>>>    End_Procedure
37514>>>
37514>>>End_Object
